					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records an endowment of land made by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Dantipanmamaṅgalam</hi> a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> on the northern bank of the river, to provide for the (daily) procession of the god within the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi>, in the temple of Amarēśvara-Perumāḷ of their village. The inscription seems to be assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
